cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image segmentation and object recognition using deep learning techniques. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes an unsupervised fully connected CRF auto-encoder incorporating rich object features and a novel human-object interaction representation. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes an efficient learning and inference algorithm to allow the full connectivity of the CRF with the auto-encoder. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also possible as the paper deals with image segmentation and co-segmentation of multiple images. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a novel human-object interaction representation that could be useful in robotics applications.
